<SubSubSubSection title="Drag forces and drag coefficients">
    <p>
        The <em>drag force</em> is always directly opposed to the velocity of
        the object.  In vector notation,

        <DisplayEquation equation="\\vec{F}_{\\rm D} = -F_{\\rm D} \\hat{v}," />

        where <InlineEquation equation="F_{\\rm D}" /> is the magnitude of the drag force, and
        <InlineEquation equation="\\hat{v}" /> is the unit vector in the direction of the
        object's velocity.
      </p>

